00:22:52.710 --> 00:22:53.710
so if it is something that you are actually
interested as well.

00:22:53.710 --> 00:22:54.710
You know, like the muffins, the tart crusts.

00:22:54.710 --> 00:22:55.710
Everything has been made with different kinds
of flour that I basically learned to use.

00:22:55.710 --> 00:22:56.710
But the recipes are very much French inspired.

00:22:56.710 --> 00:22:57.710
Because that's where I'm from.

00:22:57.710 --> 00:22:58.710
But they are inspired by, my travels.

00:22:58.710 --> 00:22:59.710
The fact that I lived in New Zealand.

00:22:59.710 --> 00:23:00.710
Places like this.

00:23:00.710 --> 00:23:01.710
So I like to take a French recipe that I know,
that I work with, and revisit it with my preferences

00:23:01.710 --> 00:23:02.710
and flavors that I've learned to cook with.

00:23:02.710 --> 00:23:03.710
Like, to this day, I don't believe that my
mother has ever cooked with coconut milk.

00:23:03.710 --> 00:23:04.710
That's something that I learned by coming
outside the French countryside where it's

00:23:04.710 --> 00:23:05.710
like more traditional, I suppose.

00:23:05.710 --> 00:23:06.710
Do you like it?

