&gt;&gt;Beatrice: Yes?

00:23:08.710 --> 00:23:09.710
&gt;&gt;Female #2: Why did you decide to make gluten
free recipes?

00:23:09.710 --> 00:23:10.710
&gt;&gt;Beatrice: Well, when I traveled to Peru,
many years ago I developed some stomach issues

00:23:10.710 --> 00:23:11.710
that I basically couldn't identify.

00:23:11.710 --> 00:23:12.710
And doing different research I just realized
I actually had the gluten intolerance.

00:23:12.710 --> 00:23:13.710
So it was a bit of a challenge because being
French, we have the baguette, the bread.

00:23:13.710 --> 00:23:14.710
But I was determined.

00:23:14.710 --> 00:23:15.710
I thought, if this is the price to pay, I'm
going to try.

00:23:15.710 --> 00:23:16.710
And in the end, came a wonderful enrichment
in my cooking repertoire, because I learned

00:23:16.710 --> 00:23:17.710
to use flours that I didn't know much about.

00:23:17.710 --> 00:23:18.710
Most of those flours also have much more nutrients,
protein.

00:23:18.710 --> 00:23:19.710
So in the end, it made me a better cook, made
me a better baker.

00:23:19.710 --> 00:23:20.710
It was challenging at the beginning, because
obviously, if you like to bake.

00:23:20.710 --> 00:23:21.710
Especially I love to make tarts.

00:23:21.710 --> 00:23:22.710
The French really love vegetable tarts.

00:23:22.710 --> 00:23:23.710
The crust, if you just think about the ratio
that you are used to working with, and trying

00:23:23.710 --> 00:23:24.710
to convert it to gluten-free flours, sometimes
it is crumbly, doesn't stay together.

00:23:24.710 --> 00:23:25.710
So it's just basically, I had to learn to
create a lot of formula for what I knew how

00:23:25.710 --> 00:23:26.710
to cook before.

00:23:26.710 --> 00:23:27.710
So that's such, you know, and then, I could
have perhaps try to go back to eating with

00:23:27.710 --> 00:23:28.710
gluten but I-- . First of all I felt so much
better.

00:23:28.710 --> 00:23:29.710
That there was no question.

00:23:29.710 --> 00:23:30.710
And then one thing I really enjoy is the flavors.

00:23:30.710 --> 00:23:31.710
It became really a plus rather than a minus.

00:23:31.710 --> 00:23:32.710
Yes?

00:23:32.710 --> 00:23:33.710
&gt;&gt;male #2: Looking through the book initially,
I was like, wow, [inaudible], her food photography

00:23:33.710 --> 00:23:34.710
is just awesome.

00:23:34.710 --> 00:23:35.710
But I just, how did you learn food photography
and what got you into that?

00:23:35.710 --> 00:23:36.710
&gt;&gt;Beatrice: Well, just by doing.

00:23:36.710 --> 00:23:37.710
Like Jonathan said, you know I worked in a
completely different field before, but I was

00:23:37.710 --> 00:23:38.710
always someone who was very much attracted
to visual arts.

00:23:38.710 --> 00:23:39.710
And I love to cook.

00:23:39.710 --> 00:23:40.710
So the day I decided to start a food blog,
funnily enough, the first article I ever wrote

00:23:40.710 --> 00:23:41.710
was about food photography.

00:23:41.710 --> 00:23:42.710
And I was fascinated, I remember, reading
about the fact that people had a profession

00:23:42.710 --> 00:23:43.710
of food photographer.

00:23:43.710 --> 00:23:44.710
So I thought "Wow, that's very cool."

00:23:44.710 --> 00:23:45.710
So I did like perhaps a lot of people do.

00:23:45.710 --> 00:23:46.710
When you want to do something, you just look
at who are the people you admire or what would

00:23:46.710 --> 00:23:47.710
you like to achieve.

00:23:47.710 --> 00:23:48.710
So I looked at the food magazines that I liked.

00:23:48.710 --> 00:23:49.710
Because all along before even starting blogging
I had tons of, I was subscribed to so many

00:23:49.710 --> 00:23:50.710
food magazines.

00:23:50.710 --> 00:23:51.710
Like cookbooks, I had tons of cookbooks at
home.

00:23:51.710 --> 00:23:52.710
And I just thought "OK, I like those pictures
and I want to be able to do that."

00:23:52.710 --> 00:23:53.710
So I started with a point and shoot camera
which very quickly became a little frustrating

00:23:53.710 --> 00:23:54.710
because I could not achieve the results that
I wanted.

00:23:54.710 --> 00:23:55.710
And I moved to SLR.

00:23:55.710 --> 00:23:56.710
And I did funnily enough, in my previous life,
I used to translate manuals.

00:23:56.710 --> 00:23:57.710
And I used to hate to read manuals.

00:23:57.710 --> 00:23:58.710
But when I bought my camera, I realized actually
the best way just to learn is just to read

00:23:58.710 --> 00:23:59.710
the manual, you know, how to use this thing.

00:23:59.710 --> 00:24:00.710
[laughter]

00:24:00.710 --> 00:24:01.710
So it was bit of an irony because I used to
think nobody every reads those things.

00:24:01.710 --> 00:24:02.710
[laughter]

00:24:02.710 --> 00:24:03.710
You know, and I'm actually using them.

00:24:03.710 --> 00:24:04.710
So I just worked hard.

00:24:04.710 --> 00:24:05.710
I will say like really put a lot of my passion,
a lot of effort.

00:24:05.710 --> 00:24:06.710
It's a trial and error process.

00:24:06.710 --> 00:24:07.710
You know my first pictures are horrible.

00:24:07.710 --> 00:24:08.710
But then I learned to understand light because
picture and specifically food photography

00:24:08.710 --> 00:24:09.710
is all about the light.

00:24:09.710 --> 00:24:10.710
But I exclusively choose natural light.

00:24:10.710 --> 00:24:11.710
So I learned to know when is the best time
of the day to shoot.

00:24:11.710 --> 00:24:12.710
And how to make food look yummy by working
with the light.

00:24:12.710 --> 00:24:13.710
But it's basically, I'm completely self taught.

00:24:13.710 --> 00:24:14.710
I think my passion was my drive.

00:24:14.710 --> 00:24:15.710
And I love to cook and eat, so.

00:24:15.710 --> 00:24:16.710
Thank you.

