lot, like you suggested you get saturated.

00:24:22.710 --> 00:24:23.710
Obviously, I'm constantly in touch with trends,
or what other people do in magazines.

00:24:23.710 --> 00:24:24.710
But my biggest actually inspiration is actually
traveling.

00:24:24.710 --> 00:24:25.710
You know, whenever I travel, it's almost like
you break the pattern.

00:24:25.710 --> 00:24:26.710
You just disconnect a little bit with this
kind of routine that you put yourself in.

00:24:26.710 --> 00:24:27.710
And you know, like I said, I'm just back from
a trip to France and Ireland.

00:24:27.710 --> 00:24:28.710
And even, like, of course here I eat very
similarly to the way I would eat in France,

00:24:28.710 --> 00:24:29.710
but of course I have different ingredients.

00:24:29.710 --> 00:24:30.710
I have different meals that I enjoy.

00:24:30.710 --> 00:24:31.710
And when you go to people's house and then
all of a sudden this woman makes this granola

00:24:31.710 --> 00:24:32.710
and you think "Oh, she make that.

00:24:32.710 --> 00:24:33.710
And what's this in your granola?"

00:24:33.710 --> 00:24:34.710
So it's just basically pulling inspiration
